        void setValues(List<T> values)
        Sets the property value.

        If this property is a single value property, this list must either be empty or null (= unset) or must only contain one entry.

        Parameters:
        values - the property value or null to unset the property

      • setValue

        void setValue(T value)
        Sets a property value.

        If this property is a multi value property, this value becomes the only value in the list of values.

        Parameters:
        value - the property value or null to unset the property
